author: Marcus Hutter and Marco Zaffalon
title: Distribution of Mutual Information from Complete and Incomplete Data
window: The remaining cases are described by means of the following figures. Figure 2 shows that FF allowed the naive Bayes to significantly do better predictions than F for the greatest part of the Chess data set. The maximum difference in prediction accuracy is obtained at instance 422, where the accuracies are 0.889 and 0.832 for the cases FF and F, respectively. Figure 2 does not report the BF case,
